data.chText: 与最低级别的警察谈话时用
data.enText: used especially when talking to a police officer of the lowest rank

data.chText: 警察，你的报告完成了吗？
data.enText: Have you finished your report, Constable?

means: (英国等国家中最低级别的)警察
(美国城镇中参与维持秩序、级别低于县治安官的)巡官

tr: a lawman with less authority and jurisdiction than a sheriff
a police officer of the lowest rank

value.def: In Britain and some other countries, a constable is a police officer of the lowest rank.

example.ex: He was a constable at Sutton police station.
example.tran: 他是萨顿警察局的警员。

value.tran: (英国等国家中最低级别的)警察；警员

value.def: In the United States, a constable is an official who helps keep the peace in a town. They are lower in rank than a sheriff.
value.tran: (美国城镇中参与维持秩序、级别低于县治安官的)巡官

trans: (英国和其他一些国家的)警察，警员
临时警察，纠察(英国在非常时期协助警察维持治安)
